President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. These appointments include Laurie Garduque as a member of the Coordinating Council on Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention, Tyler Jacks as a member of the National Cancer Advisory Board, Karen J. McCulloh as a member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled, Joan Ellyn Silber as a member of the Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad, and Lisa M. Wilusz as a member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled. These individuals bring a depth of experience and dedication to their new roles, and President Obama looks forward to working with them in the months and years to come.